<p itemprop="description">A lead frontend developer provides strategic leadership and technical direction for frontend development across the organisation. They define frontend architecture standards, lead major transformation initiatives, and work closely with product teams and senior leadership to align frontend strategy with business objectives.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define organisation-wide frontend architecture and development standards</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead strategic frontend initiatives and technology transformations</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide technical leadership and direction to multiple frontend teams</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive adoption of design systems and component libraries</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with product managers and designers on user experience strategy</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Champion accessibility and inclusive design practices</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent the organisation in frontend development communities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Manage relationships with senior stakeholders and external partners</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive continuous improvement in frontend development practices</li>
    </ul>
</section>

